ZH: 我经常感到抑郁症。
EN: I often feel depressed.
ZH: 抑郁症是一种常见的心理疾病。
EN: Depression is a common mental illness.
ZH: 他的抑郁症状越来越严重。
EN: His symptoms of depression are getting worse.
ZH: 抑郁症可以导致情绪低落和缺乏动力。
EN: Depression can cause sadness and lack of motivation.
ZH: 这个病人因为抑郁症入院治疗。
EN: This patient was admitted for treatment of depression.
ZH: 心理咨询可以帮助抑郁症患者恢复健康。
EN: Psychological counseling can help depressed patients recover.
ZH: 抑郁症需要长期的治疗和关注。
EN: Depression requires long-term treatment and care.
ZH: 抑郁症不仅影响身体，还影响精神。
EN: Depression not only affects the body, but also the mind.
ZH: 他的抑郁症治疗效果不错。
EN: His treatment for depression has been effective.
ZH: 抑郁症可以通过药物和心理治疗来控制。
EN: Depression can be managed through medication and psychotherapy.
ZH: 这个社区提供免费的抑郁症支持小组。
EN: This community offers free support groups for depression.
ZH: 抑郁症患者需要家人的支持和理解。
EN: Depressed patients need the support and understanding of their families.
ZH: 抑郁症的症状包括无法入睡和食欲不振。
EN: Symptoms of depression include insomnia and loss of appetite.
ZH: 他的抑郁症让他无法专注于工作。
EN: His depression prevents him from focusing on work.
ZH: 抑郁症使他持续感到内心的空虚和无助。
EN: Depression makes him constantly feel empty and helpless inside.
ZH: 抑郁症不能被轻视或忽视。
EN: Depression should not be underestimated or ignored.
ZH: 抑郁症会对日常生活造成严重的影响。
EN: Depression can have a serious impact on daily life.
ZH: 抑郁症不是自己能够摆脱的。
EN: Depression is not something you can overcome on your own.
ZH: 患有抑郁症的人需要寻求专业的帮助。
EN: People with depression need to seek professional help.
ZH: 抑郁症是可以治愈的，不要放弃治疗。
EN: Depression is curable, don't give up on treatment.
